{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":81365,"duration_api_ms":80783,"num_turns":17,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a627ba42-079e-4ea5-a204-08aee6f32974","total_cost_usd":0.68457875,"usage":{"input_tokens":11,"cache_creation_input_tokens":53861,"cache_read_input_tokens":530085,"output_tokens":3314,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":53861,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":11,"outputTokens":3314,"cacheReadInputTokens":530085,"cacheCreationInputTokens":53861,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.68457875,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"evidence":["All 67 milestone_record tests pass (0 failures, 0 ignored)","cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes cleanly","cargo fmt --all --check passes (no formatting issues)","model.rs: TaskRunEntry has all required fields — milestone_id (line 275), bead_id (278), project_id (280), run_id (282), plan_hash (285), outcome (288), outcome_detail (290), started_at (293), finished_at (296) — all new optional fields use serde(default, skip_serializing_if) for backward compatibility","model.rs: MilestoneProgress.skipped_beads (line 203) with serde(default), remaining() accounts for it (line 213)","model.rs: MilestoneEventType::BeadSkipped variant (line 240) enables proper journal tracking of skipped runs","model.rs: TaskRunOutcome::Skipped variant (line 306) with is_terminal() returning true (line 311)","service.rs: TaskRunLineagePort trait (lines 65-100) defines read_task_runs, append_task_run, update_task_run, and find_runs_for_bead","service.rs: record_bead_start (line 268) accepts and persists run_id and plan_hash in new TaskRunEntry","service.rs: record_bead_completion (line 329) delegates entirely to update_task_run (line 344) — single completion path, no second append","service.rs: update_task_run (line 395) correctly sequences lineage → snapshot → journal writes; validates terminal outcome (line 409); updates counters for Succeeded/Failed/Skipped (lines 431-442); clears active_bead (lines 448-453)","service.rs: Non-transactional write ordering is documented (lines 390-393): lineage is source of truth, snapshot and journal are follow-up writes that may be temporarily inconsistent after crash","fs.rs: FsTaskRunLineageStore has same_attempt() (line 2301), is_superseded_legacy_start() (line 2307), merge_attempt_rows() (line 2317), and collapse_runs_for_bead() (line 2334) for legacy paired-row handling","fs.rs: update_task_run (line 2414) uses AdvisoryFileLock (line 2427); run_id-aware disambiguation (lines 2471-2543); legacy start rows filtered via is_superseded_legacy_start (lines 2486, 2527)","fs.rs: Terminal-rejection error at line 2546-2556 now includes run_id when available via run_suffix","fs.rs: find_runs_for_bead (line 2577) delegates to collapse_runs_for_bead for legacy pair collapsing before sorting","Test: find_runs_for_bead_collapses_legacy_start_completion_pairs (line 957) seeds paired running+terminal rows, verifies collapse to 2 entries with only terminal outcomes visible","Test: legacy_paired_rows_do_not_block_no_run_id_retry_finalization (line 1221) seeds legacy paired rows, appends a new retry without run_id, finalizes it successfully, verifies 3 raw rows collapse to 2 via find_runs_for_bead","Test: multiple_retries_visible_for_same_bead (line 1131) covers start→fail→start→succeed cycle with both attempts visible","Test: completion_flow_rejects_duplicate_finalization (line 1388) verifies already-finalized error","Test: lineage_updates_require_run_id_when_multiple_open_attempts_exist (line 1458) verifies ambiguity rejection and exact run_id matching","Test: task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields (line 774) verifies old JSON without new fields deserializes correctly"],"findings_or_gaps":["The non-transactional lineage→snapshot→journal write ordering is now documented in service.rs (lines 390-393), acknowledging that crash between writes can leave snapshot/journal behind lineage. No reconciliation function exists yet, but lineage is explicitly designated as the repair source of truth — an acceptable state for file-based storage.","AppError::RunStartFailed is used (service.rs line 410) for rejecting non-terminal outcomes in update_task_run, which is semantically a finalization rejection. A more specific variant would be clearer, but this is cosmetic, not a correctness issue.","The is_superseded_legacy_start helper (fs.rs line 2307) performs an O(n) scan over all entries for each candidate in the open_matches filter. For typical milestone sizes (tens of entries) this is negligible, but worth noting for awareness.","find_runs_for_bead does not acquire the advisory lock during reads (fs.rs line 2583). This is acceptable for the current single-writer model but could lead to torn reads under concurrent writers."],"follow_up_or_amendments":[],"outcome":"approved"},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"c855e457-279d-4454-90e5-ef5f912c00a9"}
